n\n==Records and achievements==\n\n====Titans/Oilers franchise records====\n* Most Punt Yards (career): 38,533\n* Most Punt Yards (season): 4,175 (2015)\n* Most Punt Yards (game): 549 (2017-10-08 @MIA)\n* Most Yards / Punt (career): 45.9\n* Most Yards / Punt (season): 49.7 (2017)\n* Most Yards / Punt (game): 56.8 (2017-09-24 SEA)\n* Most Yards / Punt (playoff career): 47.1\n\n==Personal life==\nKern is the son of [[Cal Kern]], owner of the amateur [[Niagara Power]] baseball team.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.titansonline.com/news/brett-kern-to-host-texas-hold-em-fundraiser-april-13-9829806 |title=Brett Kern to Host Texas Hold 'em Fundraiser April 13 |last=Peters |first=Craig |work=Titans Online |access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref> Kern is married to Tiffany Kern and the couple has three kids, Bryce Jeremiah, Anelle Naomi, and Quinn Eliana. Kern is an avid golfer that sports a +1 handicap. He picked the game up late in his high school years and caddied for three summers at Inverness Golf Club while in college. The course is located in Toledo, Ohio, and has hosted PGA and NCAA Championships. In 2011, Kern competed in The Vinny, a local golf fundraising tournament hosted by singers Vince Gill and Amy Grant, and finished fourth in the event.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brett Kern|url=https://www.titansonline.com/team/players-roster/brett-kern/|website=TitansOnline.com|date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.denverbroncos.com/page.php?id=498&contentID=8675 Denver Broncos bio]\n*[http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000477236/article/titans-brett-kern-agree-on-multiyear-contract]\n{{Tennessee Titans roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kern, Brett}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Conference Pro Bowl players]]\n[[Category:American football punters]]\n[[Category:Denver Broncos players]]\n[[Category:People from Grand Island, New York]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from New York (state)]